  "text": "Canine models have the advantages of providing consecutive data on the plasma concentration of individuals, allowing the use of formulations, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ease of handling, and an abundance of background data. Dogs thus are widely used for pharmacokinetic and toxicokinetic studies. However, they occasionally show individual variability in the plasma concentration after oral administration.",
